cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for centerline extraction, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions the use of a fully convolutional network (FCN), which is a popular deep learning architecture for image segmentation tasks, indicating that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a minimal path extractor, which is a technique used in computational geometry, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.MS (Mathematical Software) or cs.CG (Computational Geometry). Finally, the paper involves the extraction of centerlines from medical images, which may also suggest that it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as medical image analysis is a common application area for neural networks.
